ZCZC EE11
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 252300 UTC
A BROAD AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1021 LIES OVER THE N SEA AT THE BEGINNING
OF THIS PERIOD SOMEWHAT RIDGING TOWARDS THE W AND SW WITH THE AZORES HIGH.
THE N SEA HIGH BUILDS FURTHER ON FRIDAY REACHING 1025 THEN REACHING 1031
BY SATURDAY WHILE KEEPING A VAST AREA OF LOW PRESSURE FAR AWAY OVER THE
N ATLANTIC. THE LOW EVENTUALLY MOVS CLOSER TO W ICELAND ON SUNDAY 985 BY
NOON WKN THE PRESSURE FIELD OVER THE NW UK. LATE ON SUNDAY THE N SEA HIGH
MOVS TOWARDS GERMANY AND POLAND ALLOWING A CYCLONIC CIRCULATION TO BECOME
ESTABLISHED OVER THE UK. MUCH OF NITON IS EXP TO REMAIN UNDER THE PROTECTION
OF THE AZORES HIGH EXCEPT S FITZROY DUE TO A LOW PRESSURE DEVELOPING OVER
THE IBERIAN PENINSULA. WHILE NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS NITON INITIALLY
STRG WINDS MAY CREEP INTO NW SHANNON AT TIMES OFTEN MODERATING SOON AFTER.
STRG WINDS THEN OCNL DEVELOPING ACROSS S FITZROY ON SUNDAY
